{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Euy2ELT55Suszf5558uwCK","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `es-http` service selects pods with `app=elasticsearch`. The endpoints are pointing to 3 IPs. Now let me check if the `elasticsearch` pods are accessible and if they have the auth setup. The precondition was failing with exit code 52 which is \"empty reply from server\" - this usually means the connection was refused or the server closed the connection without responding.\n\nWait - looking at the service manifest, the port is named \"https\" - which suggests it might be SSL/TLS. But the curl commands were using `http://` not `https://`. Let me check the elasticsearch pod to see if it's listening on HTTP or HTTPS.\nI'm seeing the precondition is trying to reach the cluster with HTTP while the service port is labeled as HTTPS, and it's using the `-k` flag to ignore SSL verification. Let me test the connection directly from the curl-test pod to see what's actually happening.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":973,"cache_read_input_tokens":34619,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":973},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ac06b237-4d22-4c28-be56-46293709e537","uuid":"d1df6ae5-9ff8-4ccd-935b-3cfd81b886db","request_id":"req_011CcMzRG1Upsx2cmpjV2gAQ"}
